'''Ted Burnett''' (b. [[November 8]], [[1920s|1926]])<ref name="This Week" /> was an actor who portrayed the [[bartender]] [[Wuher]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="TAoSW">[[The Art of Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope|''The Art of Star Wars'']] {{C|page 60}}</ref> For his three lines of dialogue, his voice was dubbed over with that of an uncredited American actor. Burnett's own, cockney-accented reading of his first two lines - telling [[Luke Skywalker]] that his [[droid]]s must wait outside the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina|Cantina]] - can be heard in the rough cut Cantina sequence in the ''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]'' CD-ROM, and his reading of his third and final line - pleading with [[Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and Doctor [[Cornelius Evazan|Evazan]] not to use blasters when the two engage in an altercation - can be heard in the first theatrical trailer for the film.

